šIn Loving Memory of
Rev. Roy Victor Bagley
12.8.33 ~ 29.1.14
Softly the leaves of memory fall,
Gently I gather and treasure then all,
Unseen, unheard,
You are always near,
So missed, So loved, So very dear."“
’In loving memory of Dad and Grandad,
William James Broome.
1931-2021
Mum and Grandma,
Joan Broome.
1945 - 2021
Both sadly missed and forever in our hearts
The most important thing is, even if we are apart,
I'll always be with you.""¾
